This paper introduces a new selection scheme in cellular genetic algorithms, which is a technique commonly used in optimization problems. The paper discusses the impact of this new scheme on the selective pressure and the emergence of niches, which are topics related to neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also presents experimental results and discusses the performance of the algorithm, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE, followed by cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.LG, and cs.SY.
